****************** INSCRIPTIONS OPEN *******************

         CNRS THEMATIC SCHOOL: BDA MDD
         20 - 25 June 2020, Bastia, Corsica, France
http://cedric.cnam.fr/lab/confs/mdd2020/

The "Distributed Data Masses" (MDD) thematic school is promoted by the 
database research community. It
aims to complete the annual French national conference "Data Management 
- Principles, Technologies and
Applications (BDA)",  whose consistent quality is recognized nationally 
and internationally. The BDA
steering committee wished to reinforce the pedagogical component 
(tutorials) within the framework of
an independent event, a desire which gave birth to the MDD school held 
in Les Houches in 2010, Aussois
in 2012, Oléron in 2014, Urrugne in 2016, and finally Aussois in 2018.

This year, we booked the IGESA centre in Bastia, Corsica. Registration 
is now open. Please note that
the number of participants is limited.

The program of this 6th edition is indicated below with a classical 
format of tutorial in the morning
and practical session in the afternoon, given in English (interactions 
possible in French):

Saturday 20/6 afternoon:
Arrival

Sunday 21/6:
Ioana Manolescu: Heterogeneous Data Management Revisited: from Mediators 
to Modern Polystores, with the
participation of Rana Al-Otaibi, Maxime Buron, Alin Deutsch, François 
Goasdoué, Pawel Guzewicz

Monday 22/6:
Amr el Abbadi: Blockchain from a distributed and database perspective, 
with the participation of Tristan Allard

Tuesday 23/6:
Morning – Nicolas Travers : How to conduct experiments to validate a 
research work
Afternoon – Social event

Wednesday 24/6:
Morning – Angela Bonifati : Augmenting Data Management with AI and 
Machine Learning

Afternoon – Genoveva Vargas-Solar and Jorge Garcia Flores: Training & 
deploying deep learning applications
at scale: data management challenges

Thursday 25/6:
Departure in the morning.

The target audience of this school consists primarily of young 
researchers in the field of databases as well
as in related or multidisciplinary fields (management of large amounts 
of data for scientific applications for example). By young researchers, 
we mean doctoral and post-doctoral students. The school is also open to 
more experienced teacher-researchers and researchers with the aim of 
thematic opening, the creation of an exchange network or retraining. The 
school is obviously aimed at research engineers from the private sector 
(R&D, startup, etc.).

More information & inscriptions: http://cedric.cnam.fr/lab/confs/mdd2020/

